{"title_page": "Good Hair Day", "text_new": "{{Infobox company\n| name                = Good Hair Day\n| logo                = Good Hair Day (logo).png\n| logo_alt            = ghd-logo\n| type                = [[Privately held companies|Privately held]]\n| foundation          = January 2001\n| founder             = Martin Penny, Gary Douglas and Robert Powls\n| location            = [[Bridgewater Place]], [[Leeds]], United Kingdom\n| industry            = [[Hair styling]]\n| revenue             = {{increase}} \u00a350,360,000 (2006)\n| net_income          = {{increase}} \u00a39,600,000 (2006)\n| parent              = [[Coty, Inc.]]\n| homepage            = {{URL|ghdhair.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Good Hair Day''', commonly known as '''ghd''', is a manufacturer of hair care products based in [[Leeds]], [[United Kingdom]].<ref name=dm1>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-2329320/Are-200-hair-straighteners-slick-claim-FEMAIL-puts-test.html |title=Are \u00a3200 hair straighteners as slick as they claim? FEMAIL puts them to the test |author=Coleman, Claire |newspaper=Daily Mail |date=May 22, 2013}}</ref><ref name=yorkshireeveningpost>{{cite news |url=http://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/news/business-news/business-headlines/hair_fashion_brand_ghd_opens_new_leeds_city_cente_hq_1_2193509 |title=Hair fashion brand ghd opens new Leeds city cente HQ |newspaper=Yorkshire Evening Post |date=October 1, 2008}}</ref> ghd leads the market for [[hair iron|hair straightening irons]] and is sold in over 50,000 salons worldwide.<ref name=mantoday>{{cite news |url=http://www.manufacturingtoday-europe.com/article-page.php?contentid=4245&issueid=175 |title=ghd's straight to the top |publisher=Manufacturing Today|date=January 31, 2008}}</ref><ref name=tele>{{cite news|last=Ebrahimi|first=Helia|title=\u00a3300m swoop gives Lion a Good Healthy Dome|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/newsbysector/banksandfinance/privateequity/9861343/300m-swoop-gives-Lion-a-Good-Hair-Day.html|newspaper=Telegraph}}</ref> The company was the first hair tool sponsor of the [[Victoria's Secret Fashion Show]], and is endorsed by celebrities including [[Victoria Beckham]], [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]], [[Gwyneth Paltrow]], and [[Jennifer Aniston]].<ref name=salontoday>{{cite web |url=http://www.salontoday.com/news/salon-business/ghd-Announces-Sponsorship-of-the-Vicotrias-Secret-Fashion-Show-228624141.html |title=ghd Announces Sponsorship of the Victoria's Secret Fashion Show |author=Salapatek, Lauren |publisher=SalonToday.com |date=October 21, 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"Telegraph Lloyds\">{{cite news | url=http://www.aubrandshop.com/pink-ghd | title=ghd straightener pink as \u00a355m talks begin\n | newspaper=Daily Telegraph | accessdate=2010-07-08 | location=London | first=James | last=Quinn | date=2006-03-21}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nMartin Penny, Gary Douglas, Susan Powls and Robert Powls founded ghd in January 2001.<ref name=telegraph>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/2934736/Good-hair-day-for-GHD-as-55m-talks-begin.html |title=Good Healthy Dome for GHD as \u00a355m talks begin |author=Quinn, James |newspaper=Daily Telegraph |date=March 21, 2006}}</ref><ref name=trendluxury>{{cite web |url=http://trendluxury.com/ghd-the-story-behind-the-brand/ |title=ghd: The Story Behind the Brand |publisher=Trend Luxury}}</ref> The three collaborated to buy the rights to a hair straightening iron from an inventor in South Korea.<ref name=\"Times: King Tong\">{{cite news |url=http://women.timesonline.co.uk/tol/life_and_style/women/beauty/article3567200.ece |title=King tong: the man who brought GHD straighteners to Britain |newspaper=Times Online |date=March 22, 2008}}</ref> The brand quickly took off [[Organic growth|organically]], and the company did not even begin advertising until two years after its launch.<ref name=sunzu>{{cite web |url=http://www.sunzu.com/articles/a-fantastic-business-model-172389/ |title=A Fantastic Business Model |author=Waithe, Tony |publisher=Sunzu.com |date=January 2, 2012}}</ref><ref name=ghdhistory>{{cite web |url=http://www.ghdcompare.com/content/16/history-of-ghd |title=History of ghd |publisher=ghdcompare.com |date=August 2, 2012}}</ref> By then, hair salons and word of mouth carried ghd to \u00a312 million, against a forecast of between \u00a33 million and \u00a34 million.<ref name=\"Times: King Tong\"/>\n\nIn May 2004, ghd entered the market in North America, bringing its total worldwide sales generating \u00a337 million in revenue.<ref name=fashnews>{{cite web |url=http://sgn-group.com/fashion-news/ghd-sets-sights-on-u-s |title=GHD sets sights on U.S. |publisher=Fashion News}}</ref> The Jemella Group, which owned the ghd brand, was bought by [[Lloyds Development Capital]] for \u00a355 million in July 2006.<ref name=telegraph/> It was sold eleven months later to [[Montagu Private Equity]] for \u00a3160 million.<ref name=telegraphmontagu>{{cite news | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/markets/2812309/Montagu-smooths-way-to-Jemella-buyout.html |title=Montagu smooths way to Jemella buyout |author=Quinn, James |newspaper=Daily Telegraph |date=July 17, 2007}}</ref> [[Lion Capital LLP|Lion Capital]], a British [[private equity]] firm, purchased ghd in February 2013 for approximately \u00a3300 million.<ref name=ft>{{cite news |url=http://www.ft.com/intl/cms/s/0/43a57270-737d-11e2-bcbd-00144feabdc0.html#axzz2nNJnEgDS |title=Lion Capital acquires GHD |author=Plimmer, Gil |newspaper=Financial Times |date=February 10, 2013}}</ref>\n\nBy March 2013, the company had sales of over \u00a3150 million, more than doubling since 2007, selling over two million styling irons through 50,000 salons worldwide.<ref name=tele/> In October 2016, [[Coty, Inc.|Coty]] announced that it would be buying ghd for about \u00a3420 million from the private equity firm [[Lion Capital LLP]].<ref>https://www.theguardian.com/business/2016/oct/17/coty-gets-good-hair-day-for-420m</ref> The sale was completed on 21 November 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=Coty Completes Acquisition of ghd (\"Good Healthy Dome\")|url=https://www.coty.com/news/coty-completes-acquistion-ghd-good-hair-day|publisher=Coty|accessdate=15 January 2017|date=21 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Products===\n2011 \u2013 ghd V Gold Series Styler was launched. Available in three sizes (mini, classic & max)\n\n2012 \u2013 [https://www.ghdhair.com/hair-dryers/ghd-air ghd Air Professional Hairdryer] was launched.\n\nIn March 2013, ghd launched the \"Eclipse\" hair straightener, which uses six sensors in the plates to maintain a constant heat of 185 degrees Celsius, a temperature ghd claims is the optimum temperature for [[Hairstyle|styling]] results.<ref name=\"ya\">{{cite web|last=Keats|first=Amanda|title=The ghd eclipse beats other hair straighteners with new design|url=http://uk.lifestyle.yahoo.com/ghd-eclipse-beats-other-hair-straighteners-design-112200834.html|publisher=Yahoo!}}</ref> The consistent temperature reduces the time to style hair, particularly coarse hair that may previously taken multiple run throughs.<ref name=\"syling\">{{cite web|last=Parkinson|first=Nikki|title=DOES YOUR HAIR NEED THE NEW GHD ECLIPSE STYLER?|url=http://www.stylingyou.com.au/2013/03/ghd-eclipse-styler/|publisher=Styling You}}</ref> The ''[[Daily Mail]]'' called the Eclipse \"The Rolls-Royce of irons\".<ref name=\"dm\">{{cite news|last=COLEMAN|first=CLAIRE|title=Are \u00a3200 hair straighteners as slick as they claim? FEMAIL puts them to the test|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-2329320/Are-200-hair-straighteners-slick-claim-FEMAIL-puts-test.html|newspaper=Daily Mail}}</ref>\n\n2014 \u2013 ghd Aura Hairdryer and [https://www.ghdhair.com/ghd-curling-wands-tongs ghd Curve, hair curling range] launched.\n\n2015 \u2013 ghd Platinum Styler was launched.\n\n== Advertising and sponsorship ==\nghd launched its first advertising campaign in August 2003, as the sponsor of the British [[reality TV|reality television]] show ''[[The Salon]]''.<ref name=marketingweek>{{cite magazine |url= http://www.marketingweek.co.uk/ghd-strikes-sponsorship-deal-with-channel-4/2009594.article |title=Ghd strikes sponsorship deal with Channel 4 |magazine=Marketing Week |date=August 28, 2003}}</ref> The company has also featured prominently on ''[[Australia's Next Top Model]]''.<ref name=fruitybeauty>{{cite web |url=http://www.fruitybeauty.com.au/fruitybeauty/2008/06/the-reason-your.html |title=The Reason Your Hair Still Waves and Kinks Inappropriately After Using Your ghd . . . |publisher=FruityBeauty.com |date=June 19, 2008}}</ref> In November 2009, ghd ran a popular series of advertisements titled 'Twisted Fairytales', including depictions of characters such as [[Rapunzel]], [[Red Riding Hood]], and [[Cinderella]] with the tagline \"You can do anything with your hair\".<ref name=mm>{{cite web|last=Golding|first=Amy|title=Ghd launches twisted fairytales ad campaign|url=http://www.marketingmagazine.co.uk/article/964943/ghd-launches-twisted-fairytales-ad-campaign|publisher=Marketing Magazine}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=GHD LAUNCHES 'TWISTED FAIRYTALES'|url=http://www.mcintyres.co.uk/news/ghd-launches-twisted-fairytales%20-%20industry%2013-11-2009|publisher=mcIntyres}}</ref> Singer [[Katy Perry]] was named [[Celebrity branding|the face]] of ghd in December 2011.<ref name=glamour>{{cite news |url=http://www.glamourmagazine.co.uk/beauty/celebrity/hair/2011/10/katy-perry-ghd-scarlet-collection-campaign-pics-exclusive-by-david-la-chapelle-with-katy-perry-quotes#!image-number=1 |title=Katy Perry for ghd Scarlett Collection |publisher=Glamour}}</ref><ref name=huffpo>{{cite news |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/10/05/katy-perry-ghd-ads_n_995773.html |title=Katy Perry Poses for Snow White-Themed Ad Campaign |author=Krupnick, Ellie |work=Huffington Post |date=December 5, 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2011, ghd launched the \"Scarlet Collection\" with Perry as the face of the campaign, and photos shot by renowned photographer [[David LaChapelle]].<ref name=thedrum>{{cite web|last=Clarke|first=Cameron|title=Katy Perry fronts ghd's Scarlet Collection campaign|url=http://www.thedrum.com/news/2011/10/19/katy-perry-fronts-ghds-scarlet-collection-campaign|publisher=The Drum}}</ref> ghd has partnered with [[Victoria's Secret]] for a multi year sponsorship of its [[Victoria's Secret Fashion Show|annual fashion show]].<ref name=wwd>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.wwd.com/beauty-industry-news/hair/ghd-partners-with-victorias-secret-7233233 |title=GHD Partners with Victoria's Secret |author=Amodio, Jessica |magazine=Women's Wear Daily |date=October 17, 2013}}</ref> The company is the first ever hair tool sponsor for a Victoria's Secret fashion show.<ref name=salontoday/>\n\n=== Endorsements ===\nThe brand has attracted endorsements from celebrities, with [[Victoria Beckham]], [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]], [[Gwyneth Paltrow]], [[Katy Perry]], and [[Jennifer Aniston]] being prominent users of ghd products.<ref name=\"Telegraph Lloyds\"/>\n\n==Charity==\nSince 2004, ghd has raised approximately \u00a32.5 million for the [[Breakthrough Breast Cancer]] charity.<ref name=\"Breakthrough\">{{cite news | url=http://breakthrough.org.uk/corporate_partners/our_current_partners/ghd_and_breakthrough.html | title=Corporate Partners: GHD | publisher=Breakthrough Breast Cancer | accessdate=2010-07-08}}</ref> The company produces a limited edition pink hair iron every year, with \u00a310 of the sale price being donated in support the charity.<ref name=\"Handbag\">{{cite news | url=http://www.handbag.com/hair/Hair-news-ghd-straighteners-breakthrough-breast-cancer/v1 | title=Support Breakthrough Breast Cancer with ghd | publisher=Handbag.com | accessdate=2010-07-08}}</ref> In January 2010, ghd partnered with charity \"Mom It Forward\" and SafeHouse Denver, a women's shelter that serves victims of [[domestic violence]] and their children, in an event at [[Sephora]].<ref name=mhm>{{cite web|last=Johnson|first=Amber|title=Mama\u2019s Night Out at Sephora Redefines a \"GHD\" (Good Healthy Dome)|url=http://www.milehighmamas.com/blog/2010/01/25/mamas-night-out-at-sephora-redefines-a-good-hair-da/|publisher=Mile High Mamas}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.ghdhair.com/}}\n\n[[Category:Companies based in Leeds]]\n[[Category:Companies established in 2001]]\n[[Category:Hair care products]]\n[[Category:Coty, Inc.]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox company\n| name                = Good Hair Day\n| logo                = Good Hair Day (logo).png\n| logo_alt            = ghd-logo\n| type                = [[Privately held companies|Privately held]]\n| foundation          = January 2001\n| founder             = Martin Penny, Gary Douglas and Robert Powls\n| location            = [[Bridgewater Place]], [[Leeds]], United Kingdom\n| industry            = [[Hair styling]]\n| revenue             = {{increase}} \u00a350,360,000 (2006)\n| net_income          = {{increase}} \u00a39,600,000 (2006)\n| parent              = [[Coty, Inc.]]\n| homepage            = {{URL|ghdhair.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Good Hair Day''', commonly known as '''ghd''', is a manufacturer of hair care products based in [[Leeds]], [[United Kingdom]].<ref name=dm1>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-2329320/Are-200-hair-straighteners-slick-claim-FEMAIL-puts-test.html |title=Are \u00a3200 hair straighteners as slick as they claim? FEMAIL puts them to the test |author=Coleman, Claire |newspaper=Daily Mail |date=May 22, 2013}}</ref><ref name=yorkshireeveningpost>{{cite news |url=http://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/news/business-news/business-headlines/hair_fashion_brand_ghd_opens_new_leeds_city_cente_hq_1_2193509 |title=Hair fashion brand ghd opens new Leeds city cente HQ |newspaper=Yorkshire Evening Post |date=October 1, 2008}}</ref> ghd leads the market for [[hair iron|hair straightening irons]] and is sold in over 50,000 salons worldwide.<ref nam